text: Rutland County is a county in the U.S. state of Vermont. In 2020, 60,572 people lived there. Its county seat is Rutland. The U.S. Census Bureau says that the county has 945 square miles (2,447 km²) of total area. Out of that, 933 square miles (2,415 km²) is land and 12 square miles (32 km²) is water. == Nearby counties == * Addison County, Vermont - north * Windsor County, Vermont - east * Bennington County, Vermont - south * Washington County, New York - west == References == Category:Vermont counties Category:1781 establishments in North America Category:1780s establishments in the United States Category:18th-century establishments in Vermont
